		<div id="comment_body_64338683"><p>Well, I don't consider Twitter that original.  It just had a very tiny bit of originality that happened to be just the right bit.</p><p>Mastodon, though, isn't a Twitter clone.  It's got a very different networking system.  Which is a part of why it's having trouble gaining more users.  I think it's a better networking system, as there's less central control, but it requires more commitment from the users.  (I as this as someone who hasn't used either, so don't take it too seriously.)</p></div>
	</div>

